rs. 5, 9 She said I have two brothers. 5 One would be 10 years younger than me and one would be a year younger. 5, 14, 20 I don’t know if she made that up because she was a storyteller too. 9, 13, 14, 15, 16 AS: I don’t know why you would make that up. 13, 14, 15, 16 No one else in the family ever heard that from her. 15, 18 She never said that to anybody else. 15 Nobody knew she was pregnant. 6, 12 AS: They wouldn’t have found you if she hadn’t brought you back. 9, 18, 19 She had hidden that from everybody.  AS: So she has a record of being able to do that. 6 LB: Yes.  Yes.  And she tried to play grandma to my kids but I was just like no. 7, 9, 10, 12 Yeah she was real frugal.  She had a lot of money but she was real frugal. 17 She would give them all a pair of socks for christmas and I got those at Goodwill and I only got them for 50 cents. 6, 9, 19 AS: Oh great grandma! 7, 11 LB: Thanks!  Just what we wanted. 9, 12, 13 A pair of argyle socks or something.  Just goofy. 9 Yet, there are so many similarities we have.  She loved collecting and antiques and I am so into that. 13 We have some similarities.  And art.  She was an artist and I kind of took that up when I was younger. 5, 9, 14, 16, 17 I don’t do it now. 14 Funny how life can… 11 Then my cousin who I grew up with as a brother, all the parents have passed away now. 5, 10, 14, 16 They are all gone it is just my brother and I and we have a couple cousins in the family. 5, 9, 12, 18, 19 Not many left.  We have a strange relationship too. 7, 9 He never married, never had kids. 15 He bought my parent’s home. 7, 10, 16, 19 He is still there. 9 Has a dog and a cat and he had retired when he was really young. 10, 12, 14, 19 He was living in Miami for many years. 6, 20 He worked at immigration and had a very powerful job with that and made a lot of money. 15, 16, 17 He moved up here and worked for Todd County for a while in the court system. 8, 9 Now he retired for good. 12, 19 He decided he wanted to go back for a w