. 9, 10, 13, 14, 15, 20 Smudging is a direct line into the human amygdala, to remind our brain centers of, ""Gaween..."" [Speaking in Ojibwe] [Unclear. 6, 9 Confirm words for translation] 7 So we smudge here.  ""Gaween..."" [Speaking in Ojibwe] [Unclear.  Confirm words for translation] 7 ""It is not without reason that we do this.""  It's part of our hope. 10 So, that's my own eccentric version...  AS: No I don't think it's eccentric.  CG: ...but I'm pretty sure that people who are not as eccentric as I am, will agree with that. 15, 18 And that's one of my essays, in my group of essays that I gave to Dennis Hisgun, is don't laugh about smudging.  Let me tell you about human physiology, neuroanatomy and how it works. 14 Smudging really works! 14 AS: Will you share some of those with me?  The essays?  Are they ones that you've written? 15 CG: Yes.  AS: Oh, oh okay.  They're not, you aren't collecting research.  CG: Nope!  Here's the deal, I got tired of not admitting that I had written them. 12, 13, 15 I gave 'em to Dennis, but I wrote 'em and so...  AS: Ah, [laughing] the truth comes out! 5, 13, 19 CG: You can go on to Barnes and Noble, or SmashWords, and you can type in Carson Gardner, and you will see an ebook on a reinterpretation of the Dao De Jing...  AS: Oh wow. 14 CG: And you will see an ebook of very eccentric sonnets, and then you will see an ebook of essays.  And, I have probably sold ten, so I am not marketing, and I don't give a damn whether you look at 'em or not. 6, 13, 20 But, if you wanna read them you can get access to 'em, 'cuz I got tired of not sharing them. 6, 12 And, I decided well, I'll put em in an ebook and then I'll die. 10, 12 And, after that people will actually look at it. 10 So, I'm hoping to become a famous dead poet and a famous dead essayist! 9, 13, 19 [Sullivan laughing.] 5 So, the fact that they're available is just a way for you to look at 'em, otherwise if you want a totally free copy instead of spending four or five bucks... 9, 1