he dumb one in the family. 12, 18, 20 I’m not the intellect.  I'm not the intellectual in the family, but I’m the only one that can function. 18 [laughs]  Yeah, you know, I’ll be the dumb one! 13, 14, 15 One of the women in one of my circles last week was talking about how she has come to learn that intelligence is not necessarily an indicator for anything worthwhile in a person [laughs]. 9, 10, 12, 13, 18, 19 She said she was married to a really intelligent person but he turned out to be mentally ill, or… 14, 19 And you know that is what the three of them are. 13, 14, 15 I do feel very separate from them. 16 It is them and me in this family of four. 18 Carey and I have constant conversations about the kids and about things. 9, 12, 16 I never address his addiction. 14, 15 He’s an adult.  He has lost all of his teeth because he doesn’t take care of himself. 6, 7, 9 He is sixty-seven years old. 20 He looks like he is about ninety.  Every email he send me ends with “I love you” [laughs]. 12, 13 He’s very, “We’re in this life together for better or worse. 11 You are what you are I accept you for what you are.”  You are a hopeless addict. 10 You are hopeless. 10 He has written three books, published them all himself. 15 Loves his children, but enables until the end. 12, 14 Ali lives with him now. 14 She went to court yesterday for some charge. 9, 14, 17, 19 I’m sure it was a possession charge. 15, 17 I don’t even ask her what the charges are anymore. 13, 15, 17 AS: At what point did you stop asking what her charges were? 9, 10, 13, 17 When were you able to detach?  We talk a lot about detaching with love. 10, 13, 17 Did that happen because of multiple disasters? 9, 12, 20 Yes.  AS: The impact of them over time? 10 JH: Yes.  AS: Or was there a moment that you remember when you were just done? 9, 12, 13, 15 I don’t think there was a moment—I am not that kind of a light bulb person. 13, 15, 16, 17 I am a slow, brooding Scandinavian. 8 Things happen over time. 12 I don’t eve