6 JH: Jarring…  a phone call is jarring for me because it is. 7 AS: So can you talk a little bit about, because we have prior knowledge of each other you never really talked about what happened to your son 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 19 Andy when he was diagnosed and what he was diagnosed with.  Can you just explain a little bit about how that happened? 9, 12, 13 You did talk a little bit about that simultaneity with Ali’s addiction. 10 You called COPE, was it? 7 He got expelled from high school for smoking pot. 8 He had never missed a day of school from kindergarten to senior year. 8, 15, 16, 17, 19, 20 Never missed a day of school. 8, 19 Got expelled halfway through his senior year because he was smoking pot in the parking lot. 17, 20 Came back and got caught. 19 I kind of knew he was smoking pot… 6, 12, 16, 17 AS: And this is when she is 19, been in treatment... 9, 16 JH: Ali is…  yes… 14 Ali’s addiction is…  I’m not sure that this thing that starts with Andy in high school. 8, 9, 11, 15 I’m not sure… 15 he’s a senior, Ali is 19, I’m not sure yet that I know she is an addict. 13, 14, 15, 20 He gets expelled, finishes with an alternative program, gets out, and then Andy got obsessed with video games. 10 He had a room in the basement and so we’d… 7 it was just me and Andy living here and my dad died. 6, 9, 12 My dad died that summer.  That was another story but I won’t tangentially go off on that but that was kind of… 9, 16, 17 I went into what I would say was just a serious depression. 9, 12 Just depression. 9 I was off for the summer.  Good and bad.  Basically, a number of things had happened. 7, 12, 13, 16 My relationship with Jill.  There were so many things that had just… 9, 12, 16 I suffered from depression. 12 Andy kind of was just doing his thing and he was starting to smoke pot and I was kind of addressing it. 9, 11, 12, 14, 16, 17 Ali was off to school and things were starting to get bad with her. 8, 9, 11, 16 I mean I wasn’t… 16 I didn’t know what to do. 13,