work for her master’s in theater education. 6, 9, 10, 13, 19, 20 She’s got her teaching degree. 20 This last half year she taught at the middle school in North Minneapolis. 8, 9, 20 I can’t think of the name of it right now. 6, 14 Now she is has a very serious boyfriend, Jeff. 12 Her hair is green. 12 I never know what color her hair is going to be. 12, 13, 14, 15 I had a horrible time; she has tattoos all over the place. 11, 17 You think my kid Spencer has always been very conservative and worried what people thought of him. 11, 12, 16, 17 She’s always very responsible about drinking and using drugs and everything, very responsible. 6, 14, 16, 17 He’s off the deep end. 12 One thing at least in dealing with addiction, it’s taught me to be very tolerant of Shelley, very approving of what her choices are. 7, 9, 13, 17 Not approving, accepting what her choices are in life. 11, 17 So Spencer’s addiction, while he was in college he had a very bad case of mono. 8 This is probably caused by all the partying. 6, 9 AS: The mono?  AP: Yes.  His doctor, probably being well meaning at the time, he had a horrible sore throat, prescribed him tons of Percocet. 16, 17 AS: For a sore throat?  AP: Because it was so bad.  AS: I’ve never heard that for sore throat. 15 Wow.  AP: It was at the time he had his first girlfriend. 9, 12 He never dated at all in high school. 8, 15 He was too shy and immature.  It was probably his first or second year. 9, 20 He met this girl Cassie who was just absolutely wild. 5, 9, 12, 17 She had no place to go so she wondered if she could stay at our house. 6, 9, 11, 12 I said, “No, no, no.”  And then, “Yes.”  Her parents wouldn’t allow her back in their home. 10, 16, 19 AS: He was in high school or college? 8 AP: College, this was after he had dropped out. 14 I said, “She can stay in a separate bedroom. 7, 9, 14 I want no interaction between you two sexually, in my house. 6, 9, 10, 13 She has to actively look for a place to live.” 10, 11 She was an alcohol