2011. 9, 11, 16 Then his addiction really got bad.  This was all out in Montana.  Jamie called us in October saying she found a pop can with some resin in it that wasn’t pot. 7, 11 AS: She was still thinking it was pot at this point? 9 AP: Yes.  I think she just got worn out, that she didn’t care what he was doing. 7, 9, 12 She needed somebody to watch Aidan. 13 Then we, in response to that, kept saying, “You’ve got to handle this yourself and do things.” 11, 16 We had no clue.  Or, “Kick him out.”  I said, “We’ll come and get Aidan. 13, 19 He can’t be in this type of environment.”  I ended up in the end of October going out there and getting Aidan and brought him back to Minnesota. 9, 12, 18, 19 AS: Just your grandson, just him? 7, 9, 12 AP: Just him. 9 Spencer said he was going to stay there. 9 He stayed out there until Thanksgiving. 5, 9, 11 We sent him money. 7 His car had died. 7 He probably sold it for drugs. 14, 20 His car had died by then. 7 We sent him money to take the train. 6, 7 Jamie had kicked him out of the house. 6, 9 Then on Thanksgiving Day he said he had to run to an AA meeting. 11, 13 He started using. 9, 11 He started pawning from us. 9, 11 AS: He said he had to go to an AA meeting but he wasn’t going to an AA meeting? 13 AP: No, he was using.  He pawned all through December 2011.  At the same time Dean’s mom was dying. 15 AS: When you say pawn, he was just taking things from the house? 6, 9, 12, 16 AP: Half the stuff we didn’t even know was gone. 9, 13, 14, 15, 19 That was so foreign.  We finally figured out he was pawning from us. 12, 13 Dean looked for his drill and he couldn’t find it. 14 “I don’t know what happened to it.” 12, 13, 14, 15 I’m trying to remember. 16 AS: Your mom was dying? 15 AP: Dean’s mom was dying. 15 Dean had to go to Santa Fe to be with her.  While he was gone Spencer took all this other stuff. 9, 19 He confessed to me that he was pawning.  I threw him out of the house. 6, 9, 15 He spent the night at a friend of his. 12,