 She was like, “No, I know Ian well.” 10, 13, 14, 15 I was like, “You don’t.” 10 But, anyway. 16 Of course the girl was his girlfriend that had gotten pregnant too was on that trip because her mother was chaperoning her older brothers. 5, 12, 15, 20 They were all friends. 12, 18 So then they were re-looking into each other.  He was a basket case on that trip.  When he came back her son and him that were best friends, he distanced himself from Ian, and I think that was the first time Ian has ever had anybody distance themselves from him. 9, 12, 18, 19 He didn’t understand what had happened. 9, 12, 13, 16 He had no clue as to why his best friend suddenly wanted nothing to do with him. 9, 12, 13 That really set him into a depression. 17 He probably was self medicating with something. 10 Jessica and I found him sitting out on the back steps crying one night. 9, 11, 12, 13, 19 We knew he had needed help for a while. 6, 12, 13 We said, “Ian, are you ready to get help?” 13 And he said “Yes.”  Jessica and I drove him to the STOP Program at Fairview Riverside in the middle of the night one night. 7, 8, 14, 19 We didn’t stop to wake up Steve. 9, 10 We just left. 9, 12 AS: What is the STOP program?  SS: I don’t know what that stands for but it’s where you can take minors for admission for chemical use. 6, 9, 12, 13, 14, 15 It is a five or six day program. 19 AS: Is it part of their chemical dependency and dual diagnosis— SS: Yes. 9, 12 STOP is for the minors.  SS: Okay.  By the time he has sobered up and realized what a mess he has gotten himself into he wants out of there and is mad. 6, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15 At that point I decided I’m not backing down. 12, 19 Jessica was rooting me on.  We got him a place at Hazelden. 11 Unfortunately, though, it was the most awful ride of my life. 6, 10, 11 You have to drive your child. 7, 14 That was the absolute worst. 9 That was the hell ride, wasn’t it? 6 I said if I had known it was going to be like this I would have gotten Steve and Jess