 Ian was—any kind of pills. 16, 17 Not even necessarily pain pills. 15 Like Ambien or Xanax.  He liked psychedelics, mushrooms, but he wasn’t using heroin. 7, 10, 18 I don’t think he even ever tried it at that point. 10, 15 He got out of Hazelden and agreed—we reached a compromise. 13 He wouldn’t go away but he would go to Sobriety High. 16 It was a sobriety high school in Edina. 8 He started his senior year at Sobriety High. 9, 11, 20 The Discovery Channel was doing a special called Cocaine Nation where they basically accused Ian of using coke and he never did. 7, 9, 11, 15 Of course, he’s got friends all over the country. 11, 12, 16, 18 AS: You mean the way they presented it on the show? 7, 16 That he used cocaine? 9 SS: That he relapsed and used cocaine. 9, 18 Which, he never had really participated in at all that I’m aware of. 15 If he ever did it was a sample.  It was never his issue. 15 He got calls from all over the country about that. 7, 11, 16 I still have it. 9 I have a copy of the show.  AS: He got calls from people… 7 SS: Friends! 12 He’s got friends all over the country. 11, 12, 16, 18 “Saw you on Cocaine Nation?  I didn’t know you had any problems with Cocaine! 13, 14, 15 Ian was like, “I don’t!” 10 He got accused of something by a girl there and thrown out somehow. 9 That is still a little fuzzy. 9 Nobody was ever very clear with me on how that happened or what happened with that. 12, 13 I thought, “Now what do I do with you?” 11, 12 Because he really wasn’t exhibiting any signs of any heavy usage at that time.  So, he went to Eden Prairie Alternative.  Somewhere in there he had started a band. 9, 11, 15 He had a little band he was playing around town and he was really getting into his music. 15, 19 They weren’t at my house a lot, they were at another lady’s house a lot. 6, 9, 17 I know there was probably alcohol involved, but I guess I wasn’t really thinking and I would put it back—it is hard to know what to let go and what not to let go. 10, 11, 13,